"{\"uid\": \"cajnewsafrica.com-2024-08-12-kenya-tops-africas-olympics-medal-haul\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Kenyan female long distance runner, Faith Kipyegon  fromMARIA MACHARIAin Nairobi, KenyaKenya BureauNAIROBI,(CAJ News)- AFRICAN countries are rolling out the red carpet for top-performing athletes returning from the Olympics in France, which ended on Sunday.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 257, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 36, \"end\": 50, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Faith Kipyegon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\"}, {\"begin\": 73, \"end\": 80, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"score\": 0.999999866747439, \"rank\": 1.2926442655459545e-07, \"text\": \"Nairobi\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Nairobi\"}, {\"begin\": 227, \"end\": 233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.5828436615954905, \"rank\": 0.7060895822666551, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The East African nation of Kenya made Africa's biggest impact at the quadrennial jamboree in Paris, finishing the highest on the continent with a total of 11 medals, four of them gold.\", \"from\": 259, \"to\": 443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 286, \"end\": 291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999290669191, \"rank\": 7.091526377344534e-08, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 352, \"end\": 357, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999683006996, \"rank\": 3.16993715553216e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The country placed an impressive 17th overall out of 84 countries that won medals.\", \"from\": 444, \"to\": 526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The achievement has underlined the East African country as a global giant, especially in long distance events.\", \"from\": 528, \"to\": 638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Standout performers in Paris included runners Beatrice Chebet, Faith Kipyegon and Hellen Obiri, much to the excitement of a country that in recent months grabbed the international spotlight over anti-government protests that left dozens dead and thousands injured.\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 663, \"end\": 668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999683006996, \"rank\": 3.16993715553216e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 686, \"end\": 701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chebet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Beatrice Chebet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chebet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Beatrice_Chebet\"}, {\"begin\": 703, \"end\": 717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Faith Kipyegon\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Faith_Kipyegon\"}, {\"begin\": 722, \"end\": 734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hellen_Obiri\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Hellen Obiri\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hellen_Obiri\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hellen_Obiri\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"President William Ruto led the celebrations: \\\"Shout out to the entire Team Kenya for the well-deserved top position in Africa.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 1032, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 916, \"end\": 928, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ruto\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"William Ruto\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ruto\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_Ruto\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are proud of you,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1033, \"to\": 1063, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"While Kenya has maintained its status as a powerhouse in global long-distance running events, the unheralded Botswana in Southern Africa pulled off a major surprise in the sprints at the Olympics.\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1071, \"end\": 1076, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"score\": 0.9999999290669191, \"rank\": 7.091526377344534e-08, \"text\": \"Kenya\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kenya\"}, {\"begin\": 1174, \"end\": 1182, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999993179, \"rank\": 7.847593548084237e-13, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 1186, \"end\": 1201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999494591534, \"rank\": 5.0540942371842174e-08, \"text\": \"Southern Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The country's Letsile Tebogo became the first African winner of the 200m men's final, to give Botswana its first gold medal in the Olympics history.\", \"from\": 1263, \"to\": 1411, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1357, \"end\": 1365, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999993179, \"rank\": 7.847593548084237e-13, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team Botswana is expected to arrive in Gaborone on Tuesday afternoon.\", \"from\": 1413, \"to\": 1482, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1418, \"end\": 1426, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 0.9999999999993179, \"rank\": 7.847593548084237e-13, \"text\": \"Botswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 1452, \"end\": 1460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaborone\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.9781564773733255e-20, \"text\": \"Gaborone\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaborone\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gaborone\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"President Mokgweetsi Masisi has urged Batswana to throng the Sir Seretse Khama International Airport (SSKIA) to give the entire team a resounding reception.\", \"from\": 1484, \"to\": 1640, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1494, \"end\": 1511, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mokgweetsi_Masisi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mokgweetsi Masisi\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mokgweetsi_Masisi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mokgweetsi_Masisi\"}, {\"begin\": 1522, \"end\": 1530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.6073550651666414e-20, \"text\": \"Batswana\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Botswana\"}, {\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1584, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sir_Seretse_Khama_International_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sir Seretse Khama International Airport\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sir_Seretse_Khama_International_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sir_Seretse_Khama_International_Airport\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I will be at the Sir SSKIA, to welcome the team,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1701, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States finished top of the Olympics medals list with 126 medals, 40 of them gold, while China came second with 91 medals, 40 of which were also gold.\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1863, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9993675272419978, \"rank\": 0.0006247060785834309, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 1802, \"end\": 1807, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.7032129862765565, \"rank\": 0.42051628516737094, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Algeria was Africa's second best at the Olympics with three medals, two of them gold, while South Africa was third with six medals, one being gold.\", \"from\": 1865, \"to\": 2012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1865, \"end\": 1872, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.8711836207293268, \"rank\": 0.14786363766658733, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1957, \"end\": 1969, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"score\": 0.9999999971787474, \"rank\": 2.821284866142812e-09, \"text\": \"South Africa\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_Africa\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ethiopia placed fourth with four medals (one gold) followed by Egypt with a harvest of three medals (one gold).\", \"from\": 2014, \"to\": 2125, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2014, \"end\": 2022, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"score\": 0.9965856634558733, \"rank\": 0.0034260341777770206, \"text\": \"Ethiopia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ethiopia\"}, {\"begin\": 2077, \"end\": 2082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9999987127595531, \"rank\": 1.2872421397833232e-06, \"text\": \"Egypt\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Egypt_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Other African countries that collected accolades included Tunisia with a total of three (one gold), Uganda with two medals (one gold), Morocco clinched two (one gold) while C\\u00f4te d'Ivoire, Cabo Verde and Zambia collected one each.\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2185, \"end\": 2192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\", \"score\": 0.9993377792017474, \"rank\": 0.0006626541056241105, \"text\": \"Tunisia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tunisia\"}, {\"begin\": 2262, \"end\": 2269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morocco\", \"score\": 0.7197948456